    verification srServeSectionCritiqueRetroGate : Test { :>> id = "63940516-2c7d-4e8f-c154-51627384c00e"; :>> title = "Sprint 154 retro gate (autonomous, D0049)"; :>> createdAt = "2026-06-24"; :>> createdBy = "claudeOpus"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::analyze; :>> procedureText = "Autonomous retro (D0049). WELL: section_json fell out of the existing view substrate almost for free (resolve_section over run_resolved + a tiny element_neighbourhood) — the D0075 select/traverse/emit separation paid off; the section's real worth is feeding the critique its LOCAL CONTEXT, which the prompt enrichment captures without a new write-trust surface. TDD held: every pure fn was red-first. AVOIDABLE-ISSUE SCAN: clippy flagged 6 lints on the first run (too-long-first-doc-paragraph x2, push_str(&format!), map_or_else, doc-backticks, single-item iter) AFTER cargo test was green — LESSON: run `cargo clippy --all-targets -D warnings` BEFORE declaring implement done, not after, since the local 1.96 toolchain (localGateMatchesCi) catches exactly what CI would. NON-blocking: the AI-critique half is unit-tested, not spawn-verified (billing) — acceptable and consistent with sr16. Estimate 3 pts held. NEXT: sr19Deliver (white-box boundary + the tier-satisfaction sweep) is the last n17 item."; }
